description: Having children, I inevitably constantly come across the state and its laws. The system of our state concerns me more and more when I go with my children to doctors and take them to school and kindergarten. I am very tired of this bureaucracy, transferring pieces of paper from one place to another. For a while, while the children were both small, I managed to avoid it. Now I spend most of my time on it. And a lot of things annoy me. At the same time, I enjoy the time with the children at home, it seems to me that they are still so free, I can observe this freedom, and it becomes easier for me to breathe.
